Text.Value: I'm Clovia Throaks, pleased to meet you! Our son Gasper has finally found himself a proper job.
No, our Gasper preferred hanging around the Guildhall. I was afraid he was going to end up as a Guild bone-breaker.
I thought you were going for a walk, Blars?
Fight? With you? Um, no. Come on, Clo. Let's head home.
Good thing I introduced him to darling Tamia Holzt. She straightened Gasper out, found him a place in the Foundry.
Depends. What's that you're drinking?
Oh, Blars! I never knew you had it in you! Let's get another bottle - and take it home!
Drink up, Blars, we're celebrating! If you won't drink with me, I bet this stranger will. Right, stranger?
Here, you can't talk to Clo that way, you... you vagabond! Take that back, or else!
You want a fight? You're on. Let's step out back.
Sewing rabbit-skin cloaks? That's all right for some, I guess, but not for our Gasper.
It's Clo's favourite, plum prosecco. I'd rather drink almost anything else, frankly.
I beg your pardon. I meant no insult to your lady.
You married a tailor? Is that the best you could do?
Clovia, you sound like an admirer of this Tamia. Are you... close?
Leave.
Serious? I'd promote him from rat-catcher! Full partner!
What are you celebrating? Maybe I will.
And he's finally made good! The lad has found himself a proper job.
Life must go on, eh? I may have an adult son, but I'm not ready to jump in the coffin yet.
You're celebrating when the city's in crisis?
I... I think I need to take a walk. In a minute.
Blars, the plum bubbles may have gone to my head, but I guess it's time to tell you.
I'm going to sell the business. The money we used to start it was mine in the first place. I'm afraid that's it for 'Throaks for Cloaks'.
No, Blars. I've been trying to tell you something all night.
Perceptive one, aren't you?
Blars, right? Are you serious about getting Gasper to join your business?
A tailor? That's good, honest work.
What? Oh. You're still here. Maybe you should take the walk.
Leave.
Aye, security at the Steel Watch Foundry. But I still wish he'd taken up the family business.
I'm leaving you. I'm starting a new life with Tamia.
Now, Blars, you know Gasper never had the patience for all the stitching a tailor has to do.
Oh, dear, the bottle's empty. Let's have another and talk about it.

Synopsis: Patrons Clovia Throaks and Blarson Throaks are celebrating their son finding a job - as one of Gortash's thugs.
